Good Design 1: Hot and Cold Water Dispenser with Clear Labels

Description:
A drinking water dispenser with two separate taps clearly labeled HOT WATER and COLD WATER using color-coded stickers. This allows users to quickly identify the correct tap and safely dispense water.

Source of Photograph:
(CAPTURED PICTURE)

Place:
VIT University, Vellore – SJT Building

Why is it a Good Design?

Uses clear color-coded labels (Red for Hot, Blue for Cold).

Reduces the chances of users selecting the wrong tap.

Easy to understand without any instructions.

Improves user safety by preventing accidental burns.

Provides an intuitive and user-friendly interface.


Benefits:

Enhances user convenience.

Improves safety.

Reduces confusion.

Suitable for first-time users.

Encourages quick and error-free usage.


Suggested Improvement:

Add Braille labels for visually impaired users.

Use larger font size for better visibility.

Install an indicator light showing water temperature.



